    "didYouKnow": [
      "The concept of 'significant figures' was developed because early chemists realized that adding more decimal places didn't make their experiments better, just longer!"
    ],
    "summary": [
      "We classify matter and use significant figures to report data accurately. Chemical reactions follow strict laws regarding mass."
    ],
    "quickRevision": [
      "Remember: Leading zeros are fake; Trailing zeros after decimal are real."
    ]
